description:
🎮Learn to create a game in Unreal Engine 5: https://www.unfgames.com/action-game

Learn to create Environments in Unreal here: https://youtu.be/1cfPiofNy-U
Learn Blueprints from scratch: https://youtu.be/W0brCeJNMqk
Learn how to model inside Unreal: https://youtu.be/9InU0xbX7l0

In this video I tried to do a "quick" look around the new Procedural Content Generation tools of Unreal Engine 5.2 but ended up with a 30-min video. Oh well... hopefully the information is clear, and you can start playing around with the tool too!

Other info I found on it after making the video:
Introduction to Procedural Generation plugin in UE5.2: https://dev.epicgames.com/community/learning/tutorials/j4xJ/unreal-engine-introduction-to-procedural-generation-plugin-in-ue5-2

You can access an example graph made by Epic by enabling the plugin content in the content browser and opening this path Engine/Plugins/Experimental/PCG/Content/SampleContent/SimpleForest/PCGGraphs/SimpleForest.uasset

Questions? Let us know in the comments!
